radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated appendix with significant periappendiceal stranding; no drainable fluid collection or extraluminal air; fluid noted within the cecum and ascending colon; clear imaged lung bases; normal heart size; liver enhances homogeneously; normal gallbladder; unremarkable spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands; bilateral renal hypodensities consistent with simple cysts; normal course and caliber of ureters; normal large and small bowel; normal bladder, rectum, and sigmoid; possible uterine fibroid; no free pelvic fluid or pelvic lymphadenopathy; no concerning bone lesions; mild degenerative changes of the sacroiliac joints and lower lumbar spine.
